Enum Summary
AbstractRootedPhylogeny.MutualExclusionResolutionMode When we request extraction of a tree with a bunch of nodes, and one of those nodes is an ancestor of the other, do we include only the leaf, only the ancestor, both, or throw an exception? BOTHNOBRANCHLENGTH is a compromise between ANCESTOR and BOTH; both nodes are provided, but all branch lengths below the ancestor are set to zero.
